The '''Mycelium pool''' is found in the northern area of the [[Mushroom Forest]] on [[Fossil Island]]. It can be used to calcify [[Fossil Island fossil|fossils]] into [[enriched bone]]s. Players can find [[Irene]] here, who will explain what the pool is used for.

The pool holds up to 28 fossils, 10 [[calcite]], and 10 [[pyrophosphite]]. The fossils can be unidentified or cleaned, however, [[plant fossils]] cannot be enriched and will be '''instantly destroyed''' if added to the pool. [[Unidentified large fossil]]s have a chance to be plant fossils, so cleaning those fossils is '''not''' recommended if planning to use them at the mycelium pool.

==Using the pool==
''Use'' the [[Hopper (Fossil Island)|hopper]] to open the Fossil Pool interface and add fossils, [[calcite]], and [[pyrophosphite]]. The items can also be selected and used on the hopper, but the current status of contents will be more ambiguous. The process begins when there are at least 3 calcite and 3 pyrophosphite added, however the exact amount of calcite and pyrophosphite required is not completely known. 10 calcite and 10 pyrophosphite should be enough for an inventory of fossils, regardless of tier. 6 calcite and 6 pyrophosphite are needed for 26 small fossils, or for 22 large fossils, 7 calcite and 7 pyrophosphite are needed for 26 medium fossils.

Once the message ''The pool begins to bubble'' is in the chat box, the chemical process begins. During this process, [[bobbing fossil]]s occasionally appear around the pool and they need to be poked back down, otherwise the fossils will dissolve from too much air exposure. If the number of calcite and pyrophosphite drops to 3 during the enrichment process, it will end and more calcite and pyrophosphite must added to the hopper to start the process again.

Using and confirming opening the sluice gate before turning the fossils into enriched bones will delete all the items in the mycelium pool.

Once the process progress bar has emptied, the process is completed, and any unused calcite or pyrophosphite is deleted. Open the [[sluice gate]] to move the enriched bones into the [[rinsing pool]] to the north, behind the [[Ancient Shroom]], where they can be collected. There '''must''' be enough inventory slots to collect all the fossils at one time.

==Using the enriched bones==
[[File:Using enriched bones.gif|thumb|left|170px|A player using enriched bones on the strange machine.]]

